    $translate['en']['fakeNews_main_title'] = "Fake news";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_subtitle1'] = "Fake news";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_desc1'] = "Recently they have become a quite popular trend on the Internet. As is well known, information spread rapidly on the web. The so-called fake news often spread faster than normal, real news. There are many different reasons behind creating the fake news - it is often urge to gain a quick and significant profit out of advertising, sometimes it may be activities done by certain countries to make influence on policy of the others (making influence on the elections results). The problem become serious enough to make companies like Facebook, Google and BBC to take actions against fake news.
In Czech Republic a special bureau was commissioned on January 2018 to deal with the problem appropriately.";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_hyperlink11'] = "A new center to fight with disinformation in the Czech Republic";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_hyperlink12'] = "False information";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_hyperlink13'] = "Spreading false information as a business idea";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_subtitle2'] = "Fake websites";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_desc2'] = "Links used in spam messages often lead to fake websites. The website is remarkably similar to the real site. The only difference between them is the address, which can be sometimes slightly different. Because of that, it is possible to steal our login details from the targeted website.";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_hyperlink21'] = "Official information from ING BANK";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_hyperlink22'] = "Phishing of personal data";
    $translate['en']['fakeNews_hyperlink23'] = "Attack on the bank's clients";
//dataEncryption
    $translate['en']['dataEncrypt_main_title'] = "Data encryption";
    $translate['en']['dataEncrypt_subtitle'] = "Data encryption";
    $translate['en']['dataEncrypt_desc'] = "Some of the viruses are capable of encrypting data on victim’s disk. After encryption of the data stored on the victim’s computer an information about what happened to his/her files and about how to recover them appears. Usually the attackers demand a Bitcoin fee to unlock the files (prices vary between 300-500$), albeit it is not a warranty of restoring the data.";
    $translate['en']['dataEncrypt_hyperlink'] = "About viruses that encrypt data";
//socialengineering
    $translate['en']['socialEng_main_title'] = "Social engineering";
    $translate['en']['socialEng_subtitle'] = "Social engineering";
    $translate['en']['socialEng_desc'] = "Sometimes it is not the software gap to be the weakest link of the system but the human itself. Social engineering is a collection of techniques, which are used to achieve a certain goal (access to the system), usually by manipulating a group of people. Directed attacks have high efficiency. That kind of attack is preluded by gathering details about the target company. Usually the company’s operations and staff are the objects of observation. Those include currently executed projects, positions held by the staff members etc.
The staff members often receive emails with supposedly trustworthy information and link, which leads to an infected website. Calling the recipient of the message to convince him/her about its credibility and reliable source is also a common practise. To make companies less vulnerable to such attacks, it is vital to train the employees about the suspicious activities. There are companies capable of performing attacks using social engineering techniques for a certain fee.";
    $translate['en']['socialEng_hyperlink1'] = "Social engineering attacks";
    $translate['en']['socialEng_hyperlink2'] = "About social engineering";
//softgaps
    $translate['en']['softGaps_main_title'] = "Gaps in software";
    $translate['en']['softGaps_subtitle'] = "Gaps in software";
    $translate['en']['softGaps_desc'] = "No system is free of flaws or oversights in their security and functionality measures. Security flaws are commonly used by a number of computer viruses. That is why it is advised to enable automatic system and software updates. Hardware gaps can also occur (such as Meltdown or Spectre)";
    $translate['en']['softGaps_hyperlink1'] = "Gaps in Windows";
    $translate['en']['softGaps_hyperlink2'] = "About the vulnerability of meltdown and spectre";
//deceiving
    $translate['en']['deceiving_main_title'] = "Deceiving belief in safety";
    $translate['en']['deceiving_subtitle'] = "Deceiving belief in safety";
    $translate['en']['deceiving_desc1'] = "As Albert Einstein once said: \"Only two things are infinite, the universe and human stupidity, and I am not sure about the former\". People usually bring problems to themselves due to their irresponsible actions. There are cases, where employees write down their login details on some pieces of paper and leave them behind on their desks. Irresponsible publishing of pictures (i.e. pictures from parties, own house, valuable items etc.) may turn out harmful to the publisher of those photos. ";
    $translate['en']['deceiving_hyperlink1'] = "What can you read from our phones";
    $translate['en']['deceiving_desc2'] = "On 21st June 2015, a cybernetic attack on the Chopin’s airport in Warsaw caused its IT systems to stop working for several hours. Almost 1 400 passengers had not departed from the airport, 10 flights were cancelled and a dozen were delayed. The experts believe that the reason of the malfunctions was a DDoS attack done by hackers.";
   $translate['en']['deceiving_hyperlink2'] = "A false belief in safety";
